 Port Elizabeth - The Nelson Mandela Bay Municipality has advised residents of a planned water shutdown on Wednesday evening. "The shutdown will be implemented from 5pm to carry out maintenance work," the Metro said. The areas affected will be: "Businesses that operate 24 hours a day will also be affected," the Metro said. "The water will be restored in the early hours on Thursday, 25 June 2020. "We apologise for the inconvenience." Follow more RNEWS articles, subscribe to our YouTube channel and for breaking news LIKE us on Facebook. For news on the Western Cape click here. For great savings on life’s little pleasures visit Bargain Buys!  Know somebody who is getting married, Wedding and Function can assist.  Have kids, then you need to visit Kids Connection. Enjoy food and travel, then visit Home Food and Travel. Need assistance with an online presence, visit Agency One. 